Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
violationBrowserReport(25.10)                    violationBrowserReport(25.10)

Name
       violationBrowserReport - Reports violations flagged by the verification
       commands

Syntax
       violationBrowserReport

       [-help]

       [-all]

       [-aclimit]

       [-connectivity]

       [-density]

       [-geometry]

       [-max_error_per_type <integer]>

       [-no_display_false]

       [-overlap]

       [-process_antenna]

       [-short]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}]

       [-report <filename>]

       [-filter <filterString>]

       [-filter_mode {AND | OR | NOT}]

       [-search_desc]

       Reports  violations  flagged  by  the verification commands. The report
       file and violation browser list the violations in the same order.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each violationBrowserReport parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man violationBrowserReport

       -aclimit
              Reports AC limit violations.

       -all   Reports all violations.

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the coordinates of the area for which to report viola-
              tions. For example, violationBrowserReport -area {0 0 100 100}.

       -connectivity
              Reports connectivity violations.

       -density
              Reports metal density violations.

       -filter <filterString>
              Specifies a text string in the violation message (in the  bottom
              portion  of  the  Violation  Browser).  When  you specify a text
              string, the Violation Browser searches the message of each  vio-
              lation and displays only the violations whose messages match the
              search conditions.

              To specify a list of strings, separate each string with a space.

              To specify a literal string with space in it, enclose the string
              in  double quotation marks. For example, you can specify strings
              such as the following:

              * METAL5

              * (600, 500)

              * METAL3 (700, 400)

              * "Pin of Net"

       -filter_mode {AND | OR | NOT}
              Specifies the condition for searching multiple  strings  in  the
              violation browser. You cannot filter complex expressions because
              the AND, OR, and NOT parameters are mutually exclusive.

              * The  AND  and OR conditions work on single strings or multiple
                strings.

              * The NOT condition works only on a single string.

       -geometry
              Reports geometry violations.

       -max_error_per_type <integer>
              Specifies the error marker number limit for each type of error.

              Specifies a limit for the number of violations parsed  for  each
              violation  type.  For example, if you set violationBrowserReport
              -max_error_per_type 500, the Violation Browser parses  and  dis-
              plays  only  500  markers per error type in the report. Use this
              parameter if you are loading a large DRC file with  millions  of
              violations  to  prevent  the  database  from becoming slow while
              loading the file and to limit the number of violations  you  re-
              view in the browser.

              By  default, the Violation Browser displays  all  markers in the
              report.

       -no_display_false
              Prohibits the Innovus software from displaying false violations.

       -overlap
              Reports overlap violations.

       -process_antenna
              Reports process antenna violations.

       -report <filename>
              Specifies the report file for the violation information.

              Type: String

       -search_desc
              Searches the description field for each marker  in  addition  to
              the table entries.

       -short Reports short violations.

Examples
              * The  following command reports all violations whose marker ti-
                tle contains METAL3:

       violationBrowserReport -all -filter METAL3

              * The following command reports geometry violations whose marker
                title contains METAL3 or tdsp:

       violationBrowserReport -geometry -filter {METAL3 tdsp} -filter_mode OR

              * The following command reports geometry violations whose marker
                title or marker description field contains Min  and  0.24  and
                METAL3:

       violationBrowserReport -geometry -filter {Min 0.24 METAL3} -filter_mode
       AND -search_desc

Related Information
       Identifying and Viewing Violations chapter of User Guide.

